	<TextRegion id="r10" orientation="0.00000" readingOrientation="0.00000" readingDirection="left-to-right" type="paragraph" primaryLanguage="English" primaryScript="Latn - Latin">
	<Coords points="255,1545 855,1545 855,1602 858,1602 858,1619 854,1619 854,1682 855,1682 855,1728 857,1728 857,1810 855,1810 855,1855 854,1855 854,1900 608,1900 608,1947 210,1947 210,1855 208,1855 208,1830 211,1830 211,1763 209,1763 209,1728 210,1728 210,1682 212,1682 212,1626 210,1626 210,1595 255,1595"/>
	<TextEquiv>
	<Unicode>Almost immediately, things started
to go wrong. Barely four months after
signing the paperwork, the contractors
revealed that their aircraft, based on an
Embraer commercial jet, was rated for
only 9 gs of force, not the 16 that the Army
wanted. Fixing the problem drove up the
plane’s weight, putting it 1400 kilograms
over its safety threshold.</Unicode></TextEquiv>
